annotationA: Uncharacterized protein; Phosphatase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: metabolic process
annotationB: Sugarlethal, isoform A; Sugarlethal encodes pyridoxine 5'-phosphate oxidase (PNPO). PNPO converts pyridoxine to its active form pyridoxal 5'-phosphate (PLP). PLP is a co-factor required for more than 100 enzymes that function in amino acid metabolism, gluconeogenesis and neurotransmitter synthesis
